dc_title_s: Sketch map of native routes from Dar es Salaam towards the head of Lake Nyassa from information obtained by Mr. Keith Johnston, R.G.S. East African expedition, 1879
dc_description_s: Routes of explorers [Stanley, Burton, Speke, Cameron, Elton, and Von der Decken] and native tracks, unexplored, are shown. Fords, ferries, settlements, halting places, and deserted sites along routes are shown. Approximate native territories are labeled. Conjectural water features shown by dotted lines. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 1 (1879), no. 7, pp. 417-22; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
